WHAT IS THIS KINGDOM
The domain that defines how artificial intelligence is architected,
trained, and deployed within the imaging pipeline. It covers the
fundamental neural network building blocks (CNN, Transformer), the
generative models that synthesize or restore images (Diffusion,
Generative Adversarial Networks), the emerging AI-native ISP that
replaces traditional hardware pipelines, AI-driven color grading
systems, generative video and film production tools, the standards
that govern AI in media (JPEG AI, ISO/IEC 6048-1, C2PA), and the
ethical frameworks that ensure authenticity, fairness, and bias
mitigation.

WHY IT EXISTS
AI is no longer an optional post-processing step. It is becoming
the primary processor of raw sensor data, the engine of creative
image synthesis, and the arbiter of automated quality control. An
imaging protocol that ignores AI is blind to the single largest
shift in the industry since the CCD. This kingdom provides the
mathematical literacy required to design, validate, and govern
AI systems in the GIOP ecosystem, ensuring they are accurate,
explainable, and ethically sound.

HOW IT IS STRUCTURED
Ten sub-domains: CNN and Transformer Foundations, Diffusion Models
and Generative Imaging, Generative Adversarial Networks, AI-Native
ISP Pipeline, AI Color Grading and Appearance, Generative Video
